Mamadou Sakho limped off against Blackburn Rovers in the FA Cup quarter-final on Wednesday . 
  The Liverpool centre back faces three to four weeks out with a hamstring injury . 
  Sakho was replaced by Kolo Toure in the 28th minute at Ewood Park . 
  He is set to miss Liverpool's clash against Newcastle United on Monday . 
  The French defender will also miss FA Cup semi-final against Aston Villa . 
 